Chilean Stocks: CMPC, La Polar and Soc. Quimica & Minera

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-09-26T19:44:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-26/chilean-stocks-banco-santander-empresas-cmpc-and-la-polar.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 3:18 p.m. New York time.  The Ipsa index rose 1.1 percent to 3,812.27. The  MSCI Chile (MXCL) 
index gained 1.9 percent to 2,086.13.  Soc. Quimica & Minera de Chile SA (SQM/B CC) gained 3
percent to 24,757 pesos, the biggest advance in more than two
weeks. Chile’s largest fertilizer producer rose today in line
with global equities as finance ministers and central bankers
urged policy makers in  Europe  to intensify efforts to contain
the region’s debt crisis.  Empresas CMPC SA (CMPC)   rose 2.1 percent to 1,707.1
pesos, its second day of gains. Chile’s second-largest pulp
exporter secured $600 million in financing in a syndicated loan
and line of credit, Diario Financiero wrote today.  Empresas La Polar SA (LAPOLAR)   fell 4.9 percent to a
record low 320 pesos. The Chilean department store operator is
seeking a strategic investor as part of efforts to avert
bankruptcy, Diario Financiero reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
 ethomson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  